block.comment: Initialize variables. Set robot variable to IP address or hostname of robot. The INFRARED sensor should be connected at port S1. Speed is initialized to 8.

custom-block.comment: Get the red ball and drop it into a red container.
Get the blue ball and drop it into the blue container

block.comment: The robot can be stopped by pressing the space key.

scripts.comment: For the ball sorter demo, the robot looks for a red ball and then places it in a red container then looks for a blue ball and puts in into a blue container. The robot's right wheel is connected to Motor B and the left wheel is connected to Motor C. An Infrared sensor is connected to port S1. The robot starts out between the balls and the containers, with the balls to the left of the robot and the containers on the right. The open arms MA should be at position 0.

block-definition.comment: This routine will look for a ball of a specified color. Before using this routine speed should be initialized and INFRARED Sensor should be set to S1

block.comment: Initialize left and right speed to 0 and tracking to false. "tracking" means that we have found the ball and are moving towards it.
continue until we have reached the object

custom-block.comment: Look for an object of ball_color and any shape

block.comment: If we don't see the object and we haven't been tracking it, then back up
if we haven't moved yet, then back up straight.
Continue turning to the right in small increments until we find the object or we have turned 3 times
If we still haven't found the object then reverse the rotations and turn to the right

custom-block.comment: This reverses the number of times we turned to the left so we should be back in center.

block.comment: Continue turning to the right in small increments until we find the object or we have turned 3 times
Calculate the direction to move based on the x location of the object.

custom-block.comment: We have reached the object. Stop moving, Close the robot arms and then move back to center.

scripts.comment: Turn the robot to the left to look for the ball

block-definition.comment: This routine will drop a ball into the container of the specified color.

block.comment: Continue until we are close to the container

custom-block.comment: Look for container of specified color

block.comment: Repeat until we've found the object or we have turned 3 times to the left
If we still haven't found the object, back up and turn 3 times to the right.
Calculate the direction to move based on the x location of the object.

custom-block.comment: we are close to the container, stop moving, Open the arms and move back to center.
